\r\n<div class=\"text-content graphic_shape_layout_style_default_External_263_338\" style=\"padding: 1px;\">\r\n<div class=\"graphic_shape_layout_style_default\">\r\n<p class=\"paragraph_style_1\" style=\"padding-top: 0pt;\">\r\n<p class=\"paragraph_style_1\">Arturo is a composer/producer born in El Paso TX. Though he showed an aptitude for music at an early age, Arturo was encouraged to pursue alternate careers, and develop his music at his own pace. Throughout the years, he cultivated his gift and established his own approach to piano and musical composition.</p>\r\n<p class=\"paragraph_style_1\" style=\"padding-bottom: 0pt;\"> In 2009, after much encouragement from his colleagues, Arturo released his debut album Cascades. Cascades debuted on the NAR World New Age charts on position number 3 which led to licensing and placement deals of several tracks. Today, Arturo resides in NYC where he is active in the music community, and continues to explore his music and composition.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n...','Biography','','inherit','open','open','','30-revision-15','','','2012-04-25 03:29:02','2012-04-25 07:29:02','',30,'http://arturomayorga.com/site/?p=94',0,'revision','',0),(96,1,'2011-05-15 00:55:52','2011-05-15 04:55:52','We are very happy to announce that composer Arturo Mayorga has dedicated the theme song If We Dont Who Will to We Sing For The World!','If We Don\'t Who Will','','publish','open','open','','96','','','2012-05-05 18:13:23','2012-05-05 22:13:23','',0,'http://arturomayorga.com/site/?p=96',0,'post','',0),(294,1,'2012-04-26 01:07:53','2012-04-26 05:07:53','<a href=\"http://arturomayorga.com/site/?attachment_id=104\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-104\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-104\" title=\"BwHeadshot\" src=\"http://arturomayorga.com/site/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/shapeimage_1-1-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>Kathy Parsons from<a title=\"http://www.mainlypiano.com/Mainly_Piano/Home.html\" href=\"http://www.mainlypiano.com/Mainly_Piano/Home.html\">MainlyPiano.com</a>was kind enough to review Cascades.<a title=\"http://homepage.mac.com/kathyparsonspiano/arturomayorga/Personal1469.html\" href=\"http://homepage.mac.com/kathyparsonspiano/arturomayorga/Personal1469.html\">Here is what she had to say:</a>\r\n\r\nCascades\r\nArturo Mayorga\r\n2009 / Arturo Mayorga\r\n\r\n4729\r\nCascades is the debut recording from pianist/composer Arturo Mayorga. Most of the ten tracks are piano with keyboard orchestration and embellishments, and several indicate a strong influence from Yanni. There is a variety of moods in the pieces - some are soft and romantic while others are darker and more powerful - indicating that Mayorga has a good range of styles. Cascades is a very strong debut even though it is a little heavy on the synth strings.\r\n\r\nSunrise begins the album with a hushed sense of mystery. As the piece evolves, it becomes more colorful and melodic while maintaining a mood of calm optimism. The title track picks up the tempo a bit. The left hand plays a flowing accompaniment to the lovely melody while gentle percussion and string washes in the background add dimension. Painting On Silence has a very strong influence from Yannis In My Time era - graceful, smooth, and melodic. Lone Walk is a favorite. Darker and more melancholy, this one reminds me of Dax Johnson in places. Piano, strings, and percussion are evocative and moody. In-Side Change is also on the dark, pensive side, and voices join the instrumental mix. Its a beautiful piece, but Im not crazy about the solo violin (keyboard). Nocturne No. 2 takes a more classical turn and is solo piano. I really like Secret Life, which also has hints of Yanni. Upbeat and rhythmic, it is one of the more joyous pieces on the album. Water Dance is another favorite. A bit more ambient for the first two minutes, the haunting flute casts a quiet spell. Then the piano comes in, swirling and dancing. Eventually, the flute returns along with strings, creating a joyous celebration.\r\n\r\nCascades is a strong and promising first album from Arturo Mayorga, a musician who obviously loves what hes doing. It is available from<a title=\"http://www.arturomayorga.com\" href=\"http://www.arturomayorga.com/\">www.arturomayorga.com</a>, cdbaby.com, amazon.com (download), and iTunes. Have a listen!\r\n\r\nKathy Parsons\r\n\r\nMainlyPiano.com','Cascades review by Kathy Parsons (MainlyPiano.com)','','inherit','open','open','','103-revision-9','','','2012-04-26 01:07:53','2012-04-26 05:07:53','',103,'http://arturomayorga.com/site/?p=294',0,'revision','',0),(98,1,'2012-04-26 00:57:54','2012-04-26 04:57:54','<a href=\"http://arturomayorga.com/site/?attachment_id=97\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-97\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-97\" title=\"Americares\" src=\"http://arturomayorga.com/site/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/shapeimage_1-300x102.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"102\" /></a>We are very happy to announce that composer Arturo Mayorga has dedicated the theme song If We Dont Who Will to We Sing For The World!','','','inherit','open','open','','96-revision','','','2012-04-26 00:57:54','2012-04-26 04:57:54','',96,'http://arturomayorga.com/site/?p=98',0,'revision','',0),(99,1,'2012-04-26 00:58:52','2012-04-26 04:58:52','<a href=\"http://arturomayorga.com/site/?attachment_id=97\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-97\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-97\" title=\"Americares\" src=\"http://arturomayorga.com/site/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/shapeimage_1-300x102.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"102\" /></a>We are very happy to announce that composer Arturo Mayorga has dedicated the theme song If We Dont Who Will to We Sing For The World!','','','inherit','open','open','','96-revision-2'